						<div class="postbody">I'm pretty sure the reason that SMB1 works is that the entire game runs in the vblank NMI. That makes synchronization pretty darn simple and its hard to get wrong. The other games that don't work probably don't work because for some reason my emulator doesn't match exactly how many cycles are run per scanline with FCEUX. At least that gives me a target. But yeah, its probably a waste of time as the smallest thing can cause an eventual mis-sync.</div>

